(en) The Churches of Dissent from above. Closest to the new church of the parish, consecrated on 28 June 1885. To the south, its predecessor is seen as ruin. The church, of medieval origin, came to decay into the discussion about the conduct of a new church building or not. Authorization to demolish it was even obtained but Lord Theodor Adelswärd intervened and commissioned the church to ruin with the maintained choir. A twenties after the time of the photo, however, a restoration of the old church would come to a stand and create a supplementary church room in the parish. The football field on the left is classic Kopparvallen.
The photograph is a contact-copied work material that does not make the airline’s finished postcard fair - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFA000032. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021018238936. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
